C="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rthen2001>rthen2001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Courage!</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#333333>(12/9/02 7:23:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=438.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mage Looking For Group</span><hr size=1> <br>
The last 4 days I have been keeping track of how long it takes for me and other magicians to get a group in PoS and PoV.  For going on 4 weeks I have had access to PoS, PoV and BoT.  Haven't spent a log of time there with trying to run a small guild and get people geared and though trials.<br>
<br>
I'm more or less the &quot;Common Mage&quot;, I belong to the vast group of semi-casual players who for the most part pay the bills and keep the servers running.  After a week of starting my exp hunt there I must say I have been shocked and reminded of how things were back in RoK days.<br>
<br>
My findings after polling 9 other mages of various guilds is that 8 of us are experiencing LFG wait times greater then 1 hour.  Generally Druids and Necros also seem to be having these issues however they can quad in tier 1 PoP zones and do not need groups as much as we do.<br>
<br>
To me PoP seems like a bring your own group type of place or a place where you need to be a Slower, Monk/SK for pulling, or a Warrior.  If your not then you can also get experice by soloing in the tier 1 and 2 zones.  Well that is if you are a: Necro, Druid, Wizard, Shaman, and a uber geard Ranger.<br>
<br>
Mages can also solo if they are content with burning all their mana on 1 tier 1 MOB then medding for 20 min.  Kei is a requirment as well.  For most mages thatmeans 1/2 a blue solo exp per hour at level 65.<br>
<br>
So unless your in an uber guild and loved in that guild expect your group wait times to exceed an hour (thats the average somm folks never got groups and loged on a twink).  Expect that soloing will be many times slower then that of even an uber Ranger.  Snare and Slow are major things in PoP and since mages lack these spells we are basiclly out of luck when it comes to soloing.<br>
<br>
I want to understand badly how anyone felt it was a good idea back at SoE to take away massive utility strength of MOD ROD 2 and then insure that soloing post 61 for mages would be nearly impossible.  I really want to understand this.<br>
Maybe at the very least giving us pet weapons that proced a 40% slow might have helped.  To expect the magician class to be suddenly desired by all exp groups was and is a bit off base to say the least.<br>
<br>
There are lots of pre 60 mages that are in for some tough times and a seriously sad awakening when they get to 61+ levels.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mages have always been able to find a corner of an expansion and solo there effectively, this has ended with PoP.<br>
<br>
I doubt anything will be done however if anyone is listening here are my reccomendaitons, do one or a bit of all of the following:<br>
<br>
1.  A pet summoned weapon spell that procs a slow..maybe 30-40%.<br>
2.  Increase the levels but not the hps or difficulty of some MOBs in ME, FG, and other older zones.<br>
3.  Introduce quest based exp (more of the PoH item turn in quest for exp type stuff, make the items eaiser to obtain).<br>
<br>
<br>
Well those are my thoughts on the Soloability situation for Magicians.<br>
<br>
