<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>My Three Easy Steps to Finding a Group</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1) Shout LFG</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Although this usually fails to produce results, it is by far the simplest way to find a group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2) Form your own group</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - See who else is LFG, and determine if a group can be made, or if a group can be nearly made.  <br>
     <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>a.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If a group can be partially formed, form it, and shout that you are looking for someone to fill in the gaps for your group<br>
     <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>b.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If 'a' fails to produce enough results, type /who all LFG 61 65 and see if there are any to fill the group.<br>
     <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>c.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If 'b' fails to produce enough results, type /who all <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>some_class</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> 61 65.  Invite people who are in non-combat zones (like PoK, or even better PoTranquility) to come join your group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3) Go around to each group and ask</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if there will possibly be room for you to join soon.  If there is not, ask the group if they can remember you the next time they are looking to fill a spot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I find that step three can produce results very often, however I placed it last because it takes the most time and it can be risky to run around asking groups.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As to your post:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1. A pet summoned weapon spell that procs a slow..maybe 30-40%.<br>
2. Increase the levels but not the hps or difficulty of some MOBs in ME, FG, and other older zones.<br>
3. Introduce quest based exp (more of the PoH item turn in quest for exp type stuff, make the items eaiser to obtain).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
#1 is out of the question because slow does not fit our class.  Not even on a summoned item.  Bluring of the classes is bad because there is supposed to be inter-class dependency.  This will never happen unless a developer is smoking from the happy tree.<br>
<br>
#2: so you want more exp from easy kills?  Honestly, when we all had 30+AA points at level 60 with Luclin gear in sebilis, we were overpowered for our environment.  To remain a fun game, there must be some challenge to overcome.<br>
<br>
#3 is an excellent idea and something they should have implemented a long time ago.  However, I do not agree that the quests should be able to be repeated.  A character flag should be given for each quest so that you can not be rewarded repeatedly for the same quest, and so that the best way to earn exp does not become monotonous.  Remember, games must have some sort of challenge to them :)  Being able to solve many quests for exp should be a challenge of the mind and of your personal versatility.  <br>
<br>
Don't forget, you still can solo in PoP.  If you kill light blues in innovation or in Justice, for example, you will earn about the same rate of exp as you did pre-PoP in sebilis.  The kills will be tougher, but youll need less of them.  I personally believe that it is selfish to think that we deserve to be able to earn the best rate of exp in the game (or something close) on our own without any help and without any challenge. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710">My Character Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
